From: lxh <lmhtq1991@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 27 May 2026 21:30:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Phase C-3a: fix STOPLESS_RUNTIME_DIR path in JvmFeatures.gmk

0081 added the stoplessgc Make block but set STOPLESS_RUNTIME_DIR to
$(TOPDIR)/../cap_runtime/stopless_gc, i.e., one level UP from
third_party/openjdk-jdk17/. Our cap_runtime actually lives in the
sibling tree `src/cap_runtime/stopless_gc/`, so from openjdk's TOPDIR
the correct relative path is two levels up, then `src/cap_runtime/...`.

Symptom under the buggy path: the `wildcard $(STOPLESS_RUNTIME_DIR)/
libstopless_gc.a` check silently fails (path doesn't exist), so the
`-I$(STOPLESS_RUNTIME_DIR)` flag is not added, and stoplessArena.cpp
fails at compile time with `fatal error: 'revoke.h' file not found`.

This patch resurrects the previously-empty 0082 (which had been folded
into 0081 prematurely) with the minimal one-line path fix.

Design: docs/c3/design.md §6 (Build wiring)

diff --git a/make/hotspot/lib/JvmFeatures.gmk b/make/hotspot/lib/JvmFeatures.gmk
--- a/make/hotspot/lib/JvmFeatures.gmk
+++ b/make/hotspot/lib/JvmFeatures.gmk
@@ -154,7 +154,7 @@ ifneq ($(call check-jvm-feature, stoplessgc), true)
   JVM_EXCLUDE_PATTERNS += gc/stopless
 else
   JVM_CFLAGS_FEATURES += -DINCLUDE_STOPLESSGC=1
-  STOPLESS_RUNTIME_DIR ?= $(TOPDIR)/../cap_runtime/stopless_gc
+  STOPLESS_RUNTIME_DIR ?= $(TOPDIR)/../../src/cap_runtime/stopless_gc
   ifneq ($(wildcard $(STOPLESS_RUNTIME_DIR)/libstopless_gc.a),)
     JVM_LIBS_FEATURES += $(STOPLESS_RUNTIME_DIR)/libstopless_gc.a -lcheri_caprevoke
     JVM_CFLAGS_FEATURES += -I$(STOPLESS_RUNTIME_DIR)
